nship with `product_options` (one-to-many). `product_options` is the \"many\" side. So, `options` has a sub-cluster.\n*   **product_options", "answer": [0], "metadata": {"type": "fill_in_the_blank", "sub_type": "how_many_clusters_have_clusters_within", "difficulty": "basic"}, "setting": {"model": "gemini-2.5-flash-lite", "temperature": 0, "flag_async": true, "max_completion_tokens": 512, "prompt_type": "only_question"}, "token_usage": {"prompt_tokens": 273, "thoughts_token": null, "completion_tokens": 512, "cached_content_tokens": null, "total_tokens": 785}}
